          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is for private reflection on religious law (smṛti). Concerns the spread of "dharmaśāsa" or "command of dharma," with offerings to all the gods (vaiśvadeva), with recitation (japa), rites of the āhitāgni (sacrificer), procuring personal gain, and other things. Text opens with a mantra dedicated to the deity Śiva.</summary>
